      • cluster

        public final Set<Set<T>> cluster(Collection<T> elements,
                                 int clusterMaxSize)
        Puts elements into sets of "similar" ones. Every object belongs to exactly one cluster. Clusters contain at least one object. If concrete match(Object, Object) method is not transitive, this produces such groups, where, match(A,B) is not necessarily true for all pairs in the same cluster, but there exists Z, such as, match(X,Z) and match(Y,Z) are true.
        Parameters:
        elements - objects
        clusterMaxSize - max. size of a cluster
        Returns:
        groups of objects
        See Also:
        match(Object, Object)
